## Version check (git)

Before API research or when verifying behavior, **check that repos are on the right version**:

- **report-portal/service-api** — For PoC we need **5.11.x**. Tags: `5.11.0`, `5.11.1`, `5.11.2`. Run: `git checkout 5.11.2` so API research matches the locked version and canonical instance.
- **report-portal/reportportal** — Monorepo; product version **24.1** aligns with our locked RP 24.1. Tags: `24.1`, `24.2`, … (no 5.11.x — different scheme). Run: `git checkout 24.1`.
- **report-portal/docs** — **No 5.11 or 24.1 tag or branch**; repo has no version tags. Leave on `develop` or use as-is for cross-check. No checkout required for version alignment.
- **report-portal-cli** — Should align with 5.11 API (check go.mod / client version). Branch/tag may vary.
- **asterisk** — May not be a git repo yet; no version check required for FSC work.

